      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "An element with position: sticky; is positioned based on the user's scroll position.",
      "html": "<p>An element with <code>position: sticky;</code> is positioned based on the user's scroll position.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "A sticky element toggles between relative and fixed , depending on the scroll position. It is positioned relative until a given offset position is met in the viewport - then it \"sticks\" in place (like position:fixed).",
      "html": "<p>A sticky element toggles between <code>relative</code> and <code>fixed</code>, depending on the scroll position. It is positioned relative until a given offset position is met in the viewport - then it \"sticks\" in place (like position:fixed).</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "Note: You must specify at least one of top , right , bottom or left for sticky positioning to work.",
      "html": "<p><strong>Note: </strong>You must specify at least one of <code>top</code>, <code>right</code>, <code>bottom</code> or <code>left</code> for \nsticky positioning to work.</p>"
    },
